# Credentials for bin/launch-platform.mjs (npm run launch:platform).
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. Every credential is optional — steps
# without one are skipped and reported, so you can adopt providers one at a time.
# All of these are one-time: they cover every current and future site.
#
# NEVER put real values in THIS file: .env.example is committed and ships
# inside the engine tarball to GitHub and every site's node_modules.

# ── Cloudflare ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# dash.cloudflare.com → My Profile → API Tokens → Create Token → Create Custom Token
#   Permissions:
#     Zone    → Zone            → Read
#     Zone    → Zone Settings   → Edit      (Always Use HTTPS)
#     Zone    → Dynamic Redirect→ Edit      (www → apex redirect rules)
#     Zone    → DNS             → Edit      (Google TXT / Bing CNAME verification)
#   Zone Resources: Include → All zones     (so future sites work automatically)
#   Account Resources: your account
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=

# Account id (dashboard URL, or any zone's Overview page, right-hand column):
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Web Analytics (RUM) site creation has NO token permission group (only
# "Account Analytics: Read" exists — you cannot grant create/edit), and the
# Turnstile step (contact-form spam protection) also authenticates with these.
# Two options:
#   a) fill these in (My Profile → API Tokens → Global API Key) — the script
#      uses them ONLY for the rum/* and challenges/* endpoints, everything
#      else stays on the scoped token above; or
#   b) leave blank and add each Web Analytics site + Turnstile widget once by
#      hand in the dashboard (the script steps will skip with a note).
# The Turnstile step also runs `wrangler secret put` in the site's directory
# (to set TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY on the worker), which uses your wrangler OAuth
# login — the scoped token is deliberately hidden from wrangler.
CLOUDFLARE_EMAIL=
CLOUDFLARE_GLOBAL_API_KEY=

# ── Google Search Console (service account — fully non-interactive) ──────────
# One-time, ~10 minutes:
#   1. console.cloud.google.com → New Project (e.g. "jacklamond-sites")
#   2. APIs & Services → Enable APIs → enable BOTH:
#        "Site Verification API"  and  "Google Search Console API"
#   3. IAM & Admin → Service Accounts → Create (no roles needed) →
#      Keys → Add Key → JSON → download
#   4. Save the JSON somewhere permanent and point at it below.
# The script verifies each domain via DNS TXT (through the Cloudflare token),
# registers the sc-domain property, submits the sitemap, and adds
# GSC_OWNER_EMAIL as co-owner so properties appear in YOUR Search Console UI.
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=
GSC_OWNER_EMAIL=

# ── Bing Webmaster Tools ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API key: bing.com/webmasters → ⚙ Settings → API access → API Key
# Verification code: it is account-wide — add any one site manually in the Bing
# UI, choose the "CNAME record" verification option, and copy the code part
# (the hex string, not the full hostname). Works for all future sites.
BING_WEBMASTER_API_KEY=
BING_VERIFICATION_CODE=

# ── IndexNow (instant Bing / AI-engine recrawl pings) ────────────────────────
# Any 32-char hex string (openssl rand -hex 16). Public by design - the same
# value also goes in each site's business.seo.indexnow_key, which makes the
# engine serve /<key>.txt as proof of host ownership. Ping after deploys with:
#   node bin/indexnow-ping.mjs <domain>
INDEXNOW_KEY=
